/* 4.10
Compare and contrast the if single-selection statement and the while iteration statement.
How are these two statements similar? How are they different?*/

SIMILARITIES
They both take a boolean a boolean condition (True/False)
They both execute a block of code within curly braces {} when the condition is true and skip the entire block of code while the condition is false.
They have similar structure

DIFFERENCES
"If" is a selection statement, "while" is an iteration statement
"If" is used to make a decision, "While" is used to create loop or repetition
"If" runs a block block of code once, if it is TRUE, while runs a block of code repeadtedly if its TRUE
"If" condition is only checked once, "While" condition is checked at every loop or iteration 

